  "stem": "<p>The perimeter of an isosceles triangle is <math><mn>71</mn></math> centimeters. Each of the two congruent sides of the triangle has a length of <math><mn>19</mn></math> centimeters. What is the length, in centimeters, of the third side?</p>",
  "answerOptions": null,
  "keys": [
    "33"
  ],
  "rationale": "<p>The correct answer is <math><mn>33</mn></math>. Setting up <math><mn>19</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>19</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>71</mn></math> gives <math><mn>38</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>71</mn></math>. Subtracting 38 yields <math><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>33</mn></math>.</p>",
